{"article_id":"QeGfCJ6XJglVXn2U","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Despite Bloody Week In Afghanistan ,","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"U.S. Pushes Taliban Peace Talks Forward","depth":2},{"id":2,"text":"With less than four days to go","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"before peace talks are to begin in Afghanistan between that nation 's authorities and the Taliban insurgency ,","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"things are not looking promising .","depth":4},{"id":5,"text":"Taliban fighters are stepping up attacks on Afghan security forces .","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"American warplanes are counterattacking .","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"And a prisoner exchange","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"that was to take place","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"before those intra-Afghan talks start","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"is being rejected by Afghan President Ashraf Ghani .","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"On Friday in western Kabul , the Associated Press reports","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"that gunmen opened fire at a largely Shiite gathering ,","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"killing at least 32","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"and injuring scores more .","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"The Islamic State-Khorasan Province claimed responsibility for the attack .","depth":6},{"id":16,"text":"All this comes","depth":5},{"id":17,"text":"after the U.S. and the Taliban","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"- but not the Afghan government -","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"signed an agreement Feb. 29 in Doha , Qatar with the stated aim","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"of `` bringing peace to Afghanistan ''","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"more than 18 years after U.S. forces pushed the Taliban out of power .","depth":6},{"id":22,"text":"Politics","depth":4},{"id":23,"text":"Trump Says","depth":6},{"id":24,"text":"He Spoke To Taliban Leader","depth":7},{"id":25,"text":"Following Peace Agreement","depth":7},{"id":26,"text":"Trump Says","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"He Spoke To Taliban Leader","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"Following Peace Agreement","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"Listen · 3:26 3:26","depth":6},{"id":30,"text":"World","depth":4},{"id":31,"text":"U.S . Targets Taliban In Airstrike","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"Days After Deal Was signed","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"U.S . Targets Taliban In Airstrike","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"Days After Deal Was signed","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"Listen · 3:15 3:15","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"`` We know","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"that the road ahead will be difficult , ''","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"said Secretary of State Mike Pompeo in Washington on Thursday .","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"`` We expected it .","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"We were right . ''","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"Despite declaring the upsurge in violence `` unacceptable , ''","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"Pompeo did not insist","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"it end altogether .","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"`` It 's time","depth":12},{"id":45,"text":"to move forward .","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"It 's time","depth":13},{"id":47,"text":"to reduce violence .","depth":13},{"id":48,"text":"It 's time","depth":13},{"id":49,"text":"to sit down and talk , ''","depth":13},{"id":50,"text":"he said .","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"President Trump also is pushing hard on the agreement .","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"By making a phone call this week to Taliban deputy leader and co-founder Mullah Abdul Ghani Baradar ,","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"Trump became the first American president","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"to speak directly with the Taliban since the 2001 U.S. invasion of Afghanistan .","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"But one leading expert on the complexities of Afghanistan cautions","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"that Taliban fighters ,","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"having secured a peace agreement with the U.S. ,","depth":13},{"id":58,"text":"may not be ready yet to sit down and talk with Afghan authorities ,","depth":14},{"id":59,"text":"whom they see as U.S. puppets .","depth":14},{"id":60,"text":"`` They want to indicate","depth":13},{"id":61,"text":"that they still have the capacity","depth":15},{"id":62,"text":"to fight","depth":15},{"id":63,"text":"if their demands are not met , ''","depth":14},{"id":64,"text":"says Barnett Rubin , a former State Department senior adviser on Afghanistan","depth":13},{"id":65,"text":"who directs New York University 's Afghanistan-Pakistan Regional Project .","depth":13},{"id":66,"text":"`` And they have the additional incentive","depth":13},{"id":67,"text":"that President Ghani said","depth":14},{"id":68,"text":"that he will refuse to release the prisoners","depth":15},{"id":69,"text":"before the talks start .","depth":15},{"id":70,"text":"So escalating militarily is a way","depth":13},{"id":71,"text":"of trying to put pressure on him","depth":14},{"id":72,"text":"to soften his position . ''","depth":14},{"id":73,"text":"Rubin notes","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"that the Taliban seem confident","depth":12},{"id":75,"text":"the U.S. will not pull the plug on a deal","depth":13},{"id":76,"text":"promising the withdrawal of all American forces within 14 months :","depth":13},{"id":77,"text":"`` I think","depth":12},{"id":78,"text":"everyone","depth":15},{"id":79,"text":"who observes Donald Trump","depth":15},{"id":80,"text":"should have concluded long ago","depth":14},{"id":81,"text":"that he 's decided to get out of Afghanistan . ''","depth":13},{"id":82,"text":"Asked during Congressional testimony this week about the Taliban 's renewed violence ,","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"joint chiefs chairman Gen. Mark Milley made clear","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"he did not consider it a deal breaker .","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"`` Yes , there was significant numbers of attacks , small attacks , ''","depth":9},{"id":86,"text":"the Pentagon 's top military official told the Senate Armed Services Committee .","depth":9},{"id":87,"text":"`` They were all beaten back . ''","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"Pompeo , for his part , went so far as to hail efforts","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"to reduce violence","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"that","depth":12},{"id":91,"text":"he said","depth":12},{"id":92,"text":"were being made by the insurgency 's leaders .","depth":11},{"id":93,"text":"`` We still have confidence , ''","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"he said Thursday ,","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"`` that the Taliban leadership was working to deliver on its commitments . ''","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"Any commitments","depth":12},{"id":97,"text":"that may have been made","depth":13},{"id":98,"text":"to reduce violence","depth":13},{"id":99,"text":"do not appear in the four-page agreement","depth":12},{"id":100,"text":"signed in Doha .","depth":12},{"id":101,"text":"Its only reference to the ongoing fighting is a stipulation","depth":11},{"id":102,"text":"that participants in the proposed intra-Afghan negotiations `` will discuss the date and modalities of a permanent and comprehensive ceasefire . ''","depth":11},{"id":103,"text":"Still , the top American commander in Afghanistan warns","depth":11},{"id":104,"text":"that the ongoing violence could imperil the Doha accord .","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"`` If the Taliban are not going to lower violence ,","depth":13},{"id":106,"text":"that causes a risk to this agreement , ''","depth":13},{"id":107,"text":"Gen. Scott Miller told Afghanistan 's TOLO news agency earlier this week .","depth":12},{"id":108,"text":"`` Which is why we 've gone directly to the Taliban ,","depth":13},{"id":109,"text":"said","depth":14},{"id":110,"text":"you need to lower your violence","depth":14},{"id":111,"text":"- otherwise , it 's hard to have an agreement . ''","depth":12},{"id":112,"text":"The Doha agreement does have language specifically","depth":12},{"id":113,"text":"calling for the release of detained combatants :","depth":12},{"id":114,"text":"`` Up to five thousand","depth":13},{"id":115,"text":"( 5,000 )","depth":13},{"id":116,"text":"prisoners of ... the Taliban and up to one thousand","depth":14},{"id":117,"text":"( 1,000 )","depth":14},{"id":118,"text":"prisoners of the other side will be released by March 10 , 2020 , the first day of intra-Afghan negotiations . ''","depth":13},{"id":119,"text":"But a joint declaration","depth":14},{"id":120,"text":"issued by Afghan president Ashraf Ghani and U.S. Defense Secretary Mark Esper on the same day","depth":15},{"id":121,"text":"the Doha agreement was signed","depth":15},{"id":122,"text":"lacks any similar specific commitment to a prisoner release ,","depth":13},{"id":123,"text":"according to Reuters .","depth":12},{"id":124,"text":"It simply calls for the Afghan government 's participation in a `` U.S.-facilitated discussion with Taliban representatives on confidence-building ,","depth":14},{"id":125,"text":"to include determining the feasibility of releasing significant numbers of prisoners on both sides . '' `` Those are n't remotely inconsistent , ''","depth":14},{"id":126,"text":"Pompeo declared","depth":14},{"id":127,"text":"when asked about the apparent discrepancy regarding a prisoner swap between the documents","depth":16},{"id":128,"text":"the U.S. signed with the Taliban","depth":16},{"id":129,"text":"and the declaration","depth":16},{"id":130,"text":"it made in Kabul .","depth":16},{"id":131,"text":"`` These were heavily negotiated documents .","depth":13},{"id":132,"text":"All the parties understand","depth":14},{"id":133,"text":"that it 's time","depth":15},{"id":134,"text":"for prisoner exchanges to take place . ''","depth":15},{"id":135,"text":"Pompeo added","depth":10},{"id":136,"text":"that the U.S. continues `` to press all sides to stop posturing , start a practical discussion about prisoner releases , knuckle down","depth":11},{"id":137,"text":"and prepare for the upcoming intra-Afghan negotiations . ''","depth":11},{"id":138,"text":"Like Pompeo , NYU 's Rubin was in Doha for the signing ceremony .","depth":10},{"id":139,"text":"He says","depth":12},{"id":140,"text":"if the document 's call for the release of 5,000 Taliban prisoners had not been included ,","depth":13},{"id":141,"text":"the agreement would not have been signed by the insurgency .","depth":13},{"id":142,"text":"`` The Taliban understood it as a commitment by the United States","depth":15},{"id":143,"text":"to get the prisoners released .","depth":15},{"id":144,"text":"That is what they 're standing firm , ''","depth":14},{"id":145,"text":"says Rubin .","depth":13},{"id":146,"text":"`` The United States is standing by the literal meaning of the words ,","depth":14},{"id":147,"text":"but trying to persuade the","depth":16},{"id":148,"text":"[ Afghan ]","depth":16},{"id":149,"text":"government .","depth":15},{"id":150,"text":"It is ambiguous in a way","depth":14},{"id":151,"text":"that diplomatic documents are often ambiguous . ''","depth":14},{"id":152,"text":"Despite his stated refusal to go along with the prisoner release ,","depth":12},{"id":153,"text":"President Ghani did meet Friday evening with U.S. Special Representative for Afghan Reconciliation Zalmay Khalilzad , the Afghan-born American diplomat","depth":13},{"id":154,"text":"who signed the agreement with the Taliban in Doha .","depth":13},{"id":155,"text":"`` Both sides talked about the future steps in the peace process , ''","depth":13},{"id":156,"text":"Ghani 's spokesman wrote on Twitter ,","depth":13},{"id":157,"text":"`` and [ the ] start of the negotiations between the Islamic Republic of Afghanistan and the Taliban . ''","depth":12},{"id":158,"text":"While those talks are slated to begin March 10 ,","depth":12},{"id":159,"text":"Barnett says","depth":13},{"id":160,"text":"that 's unlikely to happen","depth":14},{"id":161,"text":"without concessions .","depth":14},{"id":162,"text":"`` The Taliban will not agree to start the talks","depth":14},{"id":163,"text":"without the prisoner exchange .","depth":14},{"id":164,"text":"The Afghan government says","depth":15},{"id":165,"text":"it will not agree to start the talks","depth":16},{"id":166,"text":"without a ceasefire , ''","depth":16},{"id":167,"text":"he says .","depth":14},{"id":168,"text":"`` So at this point , it 's very unlikely the talks will go forward in the immediate future . ''","depth":12}],"relations":[{"parent":337,"left":170,"right":336,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":170,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":336,"left":189,"right":335,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":189,"left":172,"right":188,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":172,"left":171,"right":4,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":171,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":188,"left":182,"right":187,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":182,"left":177,"right":181,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":177,"left":5,"right":176,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":176,"left":6,"right":175,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":175,"left":174,"right":10,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":174,"left":7,"right":173,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":173,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":181,"left":180,"right":15,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":180,"left":11,"right":179,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":179,"left":12,"right":178,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":178,"left":13,"right":14,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":187,"left":16,"right":186,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":186,"left":185,"right":21,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":185,"left":183,"right":184,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":183,"left":17,"right":18,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":184,"left":19,"right":20,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":335,"left":19